    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Rough notes on another idea (more mid-term than short-term), in the direction of making integrations first-class:\r\n\r\n\"swap out \"core\" components of truffle (i.e. making `truffle migrate` itself a swappable component, along with `truffle test`\" \r\n\r\nsemi-related rough notes:\r\n\"move towards making `truffle test`/`truffle-test` itself swappable also allows us to support things like .vy testing support. i.e. the default being a .sol work flow, but being able to drop in a package that can handle .vy or some other smart contract lang testing\"\r\n\r\n(doing the same for `truffle-migrate`/`truffle migrate` also allows us to move towards integrations being first-class)",
